<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Earth is great for Kitting (but it takes awhile to learn how to do it well, with earth it is much easier.), Groups and Running away while your pet fights.<br>
Have no more then one Earth elemental in a group, but one is nessary if you don't have a druid to bind your enemies.<br>
They cast earth bind spells and have the most health.<p>

Water is great for soloing.<br>
They cause nice damage and are all around good fighters. They cast Ice spells.<br>
Great for desert or lava areas where mobs do not have any resistance against cold.<p>

Fire cause the most damage, great for groups with at least one earth elemental or druid. They are nice to use, but lacks health. Great for the north where mobs (gnolls and orcs) lack resistance against fire. I think they cast both fire shield and flame bolt. Note rain and snow may cause your spells to fizzle  more often, at least that is what I have experience.<p>

Air is great for surprise. They cast invisiblity on themselves. It looks like you don't have a pet at first. Great for large groups where pets might get in the way. They would be great for group dungeon play if you can see them.<br>
I am close to 16th lvl, I should be able to test it, with see invis or accumen spells.<br>
Most agile of the pets and hardest to hit.<p>

Get "Burn Out" when you get a chance. It really enhances your pet for a long time 15 min.<p>

Well I hope it helps!<p>

May the Elements protect you,<br>
Lord Melk</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
