<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Now just erase the message above this one from your head and listen up <img src="http://www.maximumeq.com/forum/Images/Happy.gif" border="0" align="middle"><p>

Earth are great for soloing, they cast root to keep the mob off you while you blast it away. Downfall is they have low agility and get hit a lot more than the other elementals, but there massive amount of hitpoints more than make up for that.<p>

Water are the perfect group and kiting pet, there ice spell does nice damage, they have good AGI and STR and they have the fastest Hitpoint Regen of all the pets.<p>

Air are also nice in certain situations, like dungeons, they have invisability to keep them out of trouble and they cast Stun and have high agility, but there low hitpoints hold them back from being a worthwhile pet.<p>

Fire.....Positivly useless, now let me explain, they do NOT do more damage than all the other pets. They do out damage earth and air with there fire spell but do the same damage as water. The only reason they are called the pet that does the most damage is because of there built in Fire Shield, thats the ONLY reason that they are considered the highest damage dealing pet. Now i have heard you can stack your damage shield on top of this pets but it still makes very little difference, with there EXTREMELY LOW hitpoints this pet is the worst of all.<p>

All in all I use Earth and Water mainly, i do keep Air on hand for when i go deep into dungeons with a small group, but thats a rarity<p>

(this is all my opinion based on the facts)  hehe have fun <img src="http://www.maximumeq.com/forum/Images/Happy.gif" border="0" align="middle"></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
