<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">The responses by Melk and Jay are pretty right on as far as my experience goes, the rest of these posts hardly make any sense at all.  First off, there are 4 elemental types and there is a good use for each one.  Anyone telling you not to bother with a certain kind is probably just unwilling to learn to use it properly.  Earth and water are the best for soloing in my opinion.  Fire isn't a bad soloer either if you've got Renew Elements and a fairly decent alteration skill.  The trick is to keep an eye out on your pet's heath with either /pet report health or by using F1/F8 to toggle targeting between the pet and the mob.  If your fire pet has less HP than the mob, heal it.  Otherwise sit there and med.  You should RARELY nuke when soloing with a pet.  The guy who said to burn all your mana while your earth pet roots is wasting his time.  You shouldn't care if your pet takes a beating, he'll heal faster than you can regain all that mana.  In fact, alot of times when I solo, I don't nuke at all.  If my pet needs assistance with the mob, I'll tank myself!  Yep you heard me correctly...hehe.  This way, I'm conserving mana and taking the heat off my pet so he can finish the mob off.  Oh and one more thing, we cant cast invisibility on our pets anymore.  So air is the best when you don't want your pet running off to make friends in those zones with bad pathing.<p>

Gobo<br>
Magician of the 13th blackbread<p>

PS.  How the heck do you kite with a water pet?!</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
