<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I am not an American,so maybe my English is not easy to understand...<p>

  About the pets,I always use earth in soloing.  Its root is the only way to protect you from being hit. In lower lvls,you can tank with your pet,and it is very easy. You can hold a staff which hit 15 dmg or so each time. But when your lvl becomer higher,it is USELESS at all. When LV 16,Shock of Flame does 9x dmg ,and if you still want to tank ,you must be CRAZY. All blue mobs can kill you very fast,and if you are hunting yellow or red,the pet wont be alive for a long time ,either. What you can do is nuke and nuke to make mob die eariler than you and your pet. But big nuke makes mob angry and face to you,so you need earth pet to root it. Dont forget to cast Malise if you are trying yellow .<br>
  And about kitting,use earth pet's root to kite is not good. You kite because you want to keep pet's health,but if mob be rooted,it will still attack your pet. So I dont suggest anyone to kite if you dont have SOW or JBoot. If you have ,then use WATER pet to kite. It has the best dmg of the 4 pets(Notice that fire doesnt do better if DS no work). Nuke mob,then start to run in a circle and let pet go. Press F9 to change a sight so that you can see your back,your pet,and the mob. When mob give up you and start to fight with pet,cast DD again. Dont forget to TURN OFF pet taunt. When mob gets angry and run after you again,run. It is the best way for mag to solo,but needs a large space,and SOW or JBoot.<br>
  Never use fire or air to solo. But if you are hunting green or lower blue mob,fire is worthy trying... it can save much time.<br>
  P.S. About the regan speed.when you use higher earth pet,like lv 24 which has 700 hp or more,it regans slower than you med to full. <br>
  Good luck to you.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
