<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">For not knowing english, book makes more sense than half the other people ;)<p>

"Kiting" is running the mob around.  Water is awesome for kiting.  Get SoW or Jboots, and set pet to no-taunt.  You nuke Mob, pet attacks mob, mob chases you around while pet hacks at it (and remember, pets are computer controlled and chase better than any person).  As soon as Mob gives up chasing you and attacks pet, stop and nuke it again, repeat.  At level 34 I would partner with a druid (snares, Sow) and kill Hill Giants this way and rarely get hurt.<p>

To the lower levels who can "jump in and tank for my pet", it gets rather difficult later when the mobs hit for 60+ damage, double attack, have huge AC, etc.  Trust me, you will want to Nuke at that point unless you are in a full group and doing blues.<p>

In order of HP-<p>

Earth, often a must have for soloing, root and high HP can save your life.  I don't use it much in groups as we usually have someone that can Snare.<br>
Water, great pet for kiting, also immune to poison (used it all the time while soloing Crags).  Nice DD spell.<br>
Air, used often in melee heavy groups where keeping the MoB stunned for a moment will keep the tanks from getting hit (especially if you don't have a dedicated healer).  Also good for traveling.<br>
Fire, use to kill greenies (yardtrash) very quickly.  Damage shield and DD makes it a killing machine, but very low HP.<p>

My 2cp</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
