<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Okay...i am level 35 and here are my experiances with pets thus far in the game...<p>

Earth: Great for soloing.  Mine right now has about 1400hp.  Down side is very low agility.  Up side is very high hp, VERY high str (about the same as an ogre).  The low agi makes them get hit more, which is a plus if you are using one of your damage shields.  NEVER use one of these when grouping with a necro / druid / ranger!  Root will break snare / darkness.<p>

Water: Nice group pet.  High str (about that of a Troll), extremely fast regen.  Down side is no way to keep the mob off you for soloing.  Positive side is regen factor.  Direct damage (i believe it is called WaterElementalAttack_01) is ice based.  Damage of the DD is (level of pet) + 1.  so if you summon a level 29 pet, dd will be 30.  doesn't seem like much, but it casts it every 6 seconds :)<p>

Air: Good group pet, especially when fighting casters.  GREAT agility.  Rarely gets hit, and when it does, it is usually for low damage.  Also a good dueling pet when dueling another caster.  Casts invis, which I find useless.  Casts stun instead of DD / Root.<p>

Fire: I dont care what you guys are saying, Fire is a really nice pet.  Maybe you should level past level 29 to see its uses.  The damage shield is (level of pet) + 1.  So if i summon  a level 29 pet, thats a 30 point damage shield (better than all damage shields in the game exept the level 58 druid / mage ones, and that is a level 29 pet!).  DD is a fire based nuke that is (level of pet) + 1.  Down side is they have low hp.  They have pretty good agility and str, though (agility is roughly the same of an elf, str is about the same as a barbarian).<p>

The focuses wont work until level 34, but then they are a must!  I dont really see how anyone could live without them.  By the way, pets only take experiance from you if they do more than 50% damage.  Other wise, they take no exp.<p>

Good hunting to you all, and I hope this helps.<p>

Magnia<br>
Level 35 Magician, Brell</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
