<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">MAGS!!<p>

hehe<p>

Ok Im gonna agree with what Mags said there... she's VERY right about it.  First off.. I will say this though ..once you hit 39th, screw worrying about regen rates and which heals faster.  ALL the lvl 39 pets have an EXTREMELY high regen rate.  something like 3% every 3ticks... I may be slightly off on that.<p>

<br>
It's not uncommon for a burned out and dmg shielded pet at 39 to trip for 40, bash/kick/slam for another 20-25 and do an extra 20 or so dmg from the dmg shield... meaning roughly 150-170dmg PER round.<p>

They take on a bit different roles at higher levels though, as Ive found with the 44th pets.<p>

The earth pet still is the best for soloing, the root sticks and sticks hard... playing around with Proon in EK no matter how hard I nuked him he still didn't break root.  Also it's conceivable for the earth pet to start being a tank while you just sit and heal it.  Not very effective I might add.. but if you aren't fighting a heavy hitter, aka Proon or Griffons.. it's pretty damn good.<p>

however the water pet is now starting to equal it in power easily.  Their now hit very nearly as hard as earth pets, 5-15dmg diff per strike per round.  Vast improvement over 39 where they were hitting for 15-20dmg per strike difference.  Their regen rate has also been upped... close to 3% every 2 ticks.  It's conceivable to just sit and heal the pet during a fight.. .I tried this with Droon just in amusement... it worked.. pet came out of it with half life and I came out with just under half mana.  Tried it out with Proon and resulsts were slightly less pleasing, but I never had to cast on Proon, just healed pet.<p>

The air pet however &lt;sighs&gt; is still useless except for dueling casters.  The high agility of it makes it a good interrupter &lt;don't believe it, try giving a lvl 24 or higher air pet two tentacle whips and sit back and enjoy the laugh&gt;<p>

The fire pet is by far the best group pet if you have a rooter of any type.  At 44th this pet is doing insane amount of dmg.. somewhere around the ability of doing 250+dmg in ONE round.  That's the best Ive seen so far.  However it still has the drawback that, like water pets, it'll go chasing off after mobs like no tomorrow.  Good party killer still.<p>

<br>
Anyhow.. that's just my two coppers on it<p>

Corstin Soulsbane<br>
Magician of the 44th tier<br>
Guildmaster of Forsaken Consortium<br>
Brell <p>

PS: Mags.. you better come hunt with me soon... gonna have to track you down otherwise! heh</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
