<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Actually, Air has the highest agi.  I never really experimented with dex, but all the different kinds of pets seem to proc at about the same rate.  Dex does not effect chance to hit, Verrant has officially stated this.  Water pet has more strenght than Air, and its dd is not twice the level of the pet.  That would make a level 45 water pet (possible with the staff of elemental mastery: water, so I hear) do 90 damage each round in just dd.  Fire pet's damage shield is (level of pet) + 1, as of August 25, 2000.  I did some tests in arena with this.  My level 29 pet (yellow to my friend at 27) had a 30 point fire based damage shield (the only reason I say fire based is because it was saying 'XXX is burned', so it couldn't have been the druid there who was like 53 dmg shielding my pet).  The water pet's dd was doing 30, and it was also a level 29 pet.  Fire pet will *always* have a better damage shield than you can cast, which is why it says 'Your spell does not take hold' when you try to dmg shield a fire pet.  Well, thats all I have to say on this subject.  I am not insulting you, Kjata, I am just saying that your test results differ from mine, and everyone who I have talked to's.<p>

